  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This project will examine neuronal and sensory fat perception. Our hypothesis is that
      subjects being either hypersensitive or hyposensitive for fat will show different brain
      activities. Therefore the investigators will conduct functional magnetic resonance imaging
      (fMRI) and fat detection threshold tests examining neuronal and sensory fat perception.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
